<subSubSection id="24CB1080FF9AFFC4FAB2A86B841DF86F" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFF9AFFC4FAB2A86B841DF86F" blockId="46.[151,1437,1472,1931]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9AFFC4FAB2A86B815EF8FB" bold="true" box="[199,315,1797,1823]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9AFFC4F8BFA86B835EF8FA" box="[714,827,1796,1823]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include Ubatuba (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9AFFC4FE7DA86A8562F8FB" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[1032,1287,1796,1823]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9AFFC4FEFEA86B84A6F8FA" box="[1163,1219,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The present study confirms, with detailed information, the presence of this species in 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9AFFC4F9CBA847844BF8A6" box="[958,1070,1832,1859]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
and extends the northern limit of the species in the western Atlantic superficially mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9AFFC4F939A822843DF883" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[844,1112,1868,1895]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9AFFC4F9B9A8238461F882" box="[972,1028,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
. Sequence accession number (GenBank): CCDB 1525—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FF9AFFC4F871A81E82E3F86F" box="[516,646,1904,1931]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490145" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">MF490145</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FF9AFFC4F8ADA81F833DF86F" box="[728,856,1905,1931]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490042" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">MF490042</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9AFFC4F91BA81E8409F86F" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[878,1132,1904,1931]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9AFFC4F985A81F8444F86E" box="[1008,1057,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
